  "texts": [
    "Then, we provide further analysis on error cases in existing models to gain insight on how to rectify the errors.",
    "Error Types in NER.",
    "For evaluating NER model predictions against the gold annotations, error cases can be categorized as either false positives (FP) or false negatives (FN) based on whether the model incorrectly identifies entities or fails to recognize the gold entities that is present.",
    "Within the FP, errors can occur from mismatches of type or span.",
    "Depending on the combinations of these mismatches, errors are classified into more finegrained error types, including Type, Span, Type&Span and Spurious errors."
  ],
